A R E S O L U T I O N
Honoring the Great Lakes Science Center on the One
Hundredth Anniversary of the launch of the SS
William G. Mather.
WHEREAS, The members of the Senate of the 136th General Assembly 1
of Ohio are pleased to extend special recognition to the Great Lakes 2
Science Center as it celebrates the Centennial of the launching of the 3
SS William G. Mather; and 4
WHEREAS, The spirit of our nation is founded upon, and reflected 5
in, its exciting and colorful past, and organizations such as the 6
Great Lakes Science Center play a vital role in the protection of 7
America’s unique heritage. The custodian for the SS William G. Mather, 8
the organization has used this historic vessel to help foster 9
awareness and understanding of the complex relationship between 10
technology, history, and the environment, and it is to be commended 11
for its tremendous efforts to guarantee that this museum ship is 12
preserved as a testament to the manufacturing legacy of the Cleveland 13
area; and 14
WHEREAS, Built in 1925, the SS William G. Mather operated as a 15
steamship and freighter for many years before being donated for 16
conversion into a maritime museum in 1987, and it was operated by the 17
Harbor Heritage Society before being acquired by the Great Lakes 18
Science Center in 2006. In that time, it has gained a fine reputation 19
as the repository of many period artifacts as well as for its 20
interesting and educational exhibitions, including its current 21
exhibit, Steam and Steel: Propelling the Future of the Great Lakes, 22
and clearly, it has become one of the center’s most prized assets; and 23
WHEREAS, The Great Lakes Science Center has enhanced the quality 24

